<paragraph blockId="31.[264,1324,284,998]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
Etymology. The species name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Scarbrough Table Of Contents" authorityYear="2005" box="[693,786,732,757]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Afroestricus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kimerus">
<emphasis box="[693,786,732,757]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">kimerus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, a noun in apposition, refers to Kimera of Unyoro, a prodigious hunter and the first King of Buganda.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="31.[264,1324,284,998]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
Distribution (
<tableCitation box="[470,571,812,838]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="9.[264,343,851,872]" captionText="TABLE 1. Distribution of Afroestricus species by country." pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Tables 1</tableCitation>
, 
<tableCitation box="[587,604,812,838]" captionStart="TABLE 2" captionStartId="10.[264,343,563,584]" captionText="TABLE 2. Phenology of Afroestricus species. Abbreviations refer to the months of the year." pageId="31" pageNumber="32">2</tableCitation>
; 
<figureCitation box="[618,721,812,838]" captionStart="FIGURE 194" captionStartId="70.[264,357,1870,1891]" captionTargetBox="[459,1150,1206,1854]" captionTargetId="figure-93@70.[411,1177,1171,1869]" captionTargetPageId="70" captionText="FIGURE 194. Distribution of six species of Afroestricus in Africa and Madagascar." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5050679" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5050679/files/figure.png" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Fig. 194</figureCitation>
). Known from one location in 
<collectingCountry box="[1089,1165,812,838]" name="Kenya" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Kenya</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[1225,1320,812,838]" name="Uganda" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Uganda</collectingCountry>
; collected at about 1300 meters during June, July, and August.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="31.[264,1324,284,998]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
Remarks. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Scarbrough Table Of Contents" authorityYear="2005" box="[430,673,892,917]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Afroestricus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kimerus">
<emphasis box="[430,673,892,917]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Afroestricus kimerus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from congeners by the characters in the key and terminalia (
<figureCitation box="[398,540,932,958]" captionStart="FIGURES 65–70" captionStartId="30.[264,370,1266,1287]" captionTargetBox="[313,1276,487,1249]" captionTargetId="figure-214@30.[281,1305,475,1258]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="FIGURES 65–70. Afroestricus kimerus, sp. n. Male terminalia: 65–67. Lateral, dorsal, and ventral views. 68. Gonostylus. 69–70. Aedeagus, dorsal and lateral views." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5050637" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5050637/files/figure.png" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Figs. 65–70</figureCitation>
), especially the long, flat, apically truncate, gonocoxal process and doubled notched dorsal margin of the epandrium.
</paragraph>
